The paper focuses on developing a new detection model for Data Leak Prevention (DLP) in the context of cybersecurity, specifically for detecting insider threats. This involves analyzing big text data and constructing a novel dataset containing formerly classified paragraphs from diplomatic cables. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves aspects of cybersecurity and information retrieval, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. 

The development of the ACESS system involves machine learning and classification, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
